<TITLE> Tight security plans for Language Day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)  A three-tier security will be put in place at the Central Shaheed Minar with the deployment of some 7000-strong police and 750 RAB members on the International Mother Language Day Saturday, top police official said Thursday. Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner Naim Ahmed told journalists from 7pm on Feb. 20, 6,898 members of the police will take control of the Shaheed Minar area. They will work from 7pm to 5am in one shift and another shift will work from 5am to 2pm Saturday. He said the security agencies will ensure security in Shaheed Minar area, maintain order during public show of respect at the Shaheed Minar, ensuring security for the president, prime minister and other VIPs, and maintain the traffic. "Barricades will be put in 23 places surrounding the Shaheed Minar. People will enter the it through six archways and 28 close-circuit television cameras will be installed. Besides, metal detectors will be there. Law-enforcers will be on guard in the high-rise buildings around. Women police will also be deployed and plainclothesmen will be on surveillance, the city police chief added. RAB director general Hasan Mahmud Khondaker saw the security arrangement at the Shaheed Minar and said the elite force were ready to ensure security. b
